   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Forty-one ALL HAVE SINNED Scripture: Rom 3:23 The source of man s sin Sin came from Satan.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Sin came into the world through Adam.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Man is born in sin.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Because man is the seed of Adam, man is sinful since his very birth.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Man s sinful life Man is born in sin, therefore man lives in sin.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>If man lives in sin, all his living is sinful, whether consciously or unconsciously, intentionally or unintentionally.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Give practical examples of how man commits sins.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Man comes short of the glory of God The glory of God is the standard of human morality.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The glory of God is the manifestation of the character and the disposition of God.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>This glory should be the standard for man s living and man s morality.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Whether a man is sinful or not should not be judged according to man s moral standards, but according to God s glory.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Some deeds are not sinful according to human moral standards, but they are quite short according to God s glory.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>For example, God s divine disposition is manifested when He forgives man s sins.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>But man thinks to himself, As long as I do not offend others, it is not a sin for me not to forgive them when they offend me.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>How short is this lack of forgiveness when compared to the glory of God.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>According to this divine standard, we realize that there is no comparison between man s moral standard and God s divine disposition and character.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Not only to hate people is sin, but also not to love people is sin.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Man is made according to God s image.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Man is the picture of God to express God.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>But now, because sin came in through Adam, man is full of sins and filthiness; so certainly man comes short of the glory of God.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The way to salvation Confess that you are short of the glory of God.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Christ is the effulgence of the glory of God.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Receive Christ as your Savior, and He will enable you to live out the glory of God.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Live in the presence of God by the life of Christ.</S>
   </TEXT>
